'''Immediacy''' is a [[philosophy|philosophical]] concept related to time and temporal perspectives, both [[Perspective (visual)|visual]], [[Perspective (cognitive)|cognitive]]. Considerations of immediacy reflect on how we experience the world and what [[reality]] is.<ref>[http://csmt.uchicago.edu/glossary2004/immediacy.htm]</ref> It possesses characteristics of both of the [[Heterography and homography|homophonic heterographs]] 'immanent' and 'imminent', and what [[logical consequence|entails]] to both within ontology.
